text: Matilda of England or Empress Matilda (1102–1167) was the daughter and dispossessed heiress of Henry I. Matilda of England may also refer to: *Matilda of Flanders (c.1031 – 1083), Queen consort of England, consort to William I *Matilda of Scotland (1080–1118), Queen consort of England, consort to Henry I *Matilda of Boulogne (1105?–1152), Queen consort of England, consort to Stephen of England *Matilda of England, Duchess of Saxony (1156–1189), daughter of Henry II of England ==See also== *Matilda FitzRoy (disambiguation)
title: Matilda of England (disambiguation)
